# Sentinel Privacy Shield — System Architecture

## 1. High-Level Overview
The system is composed of five major components:

1. Local Service Daemon
2. Network Interception Layer
3. Permission Firewall
4. Synthetic Identity Engine
5. Local ML Anomaly Engine

All components operate locally with no cloud communication.

## 2. Component Breakdown

### 2.1 Local Service Daemon
- Runs persistently
- Manages all modules
- Handles IPC between components

### 2.2 Network Interception Layer
- Implements local VPN
- Parses outbound requests
- Detects fingerprinting scripts
- Blocks known surveillance endpoints

### 2.3 Permission Firewall
- Hooks into OS permission calls
- Enforces user‑defined rules
- Logs unauthorized attempts

### 2.4 Synthetic Identity Engine
- Generates rotating identifiers:
  - Device model
  - OS version
  - User agent
  - Screen metrics
- Randomizes fingerprint surfaces

### 2.5 ML Anomaly Engine
- Local‑only model
- Detects:
  - Unusual network bursts
  - Suspicious permission patterns
  - Covert sensor activation

## 3. Data Flow
User → App → Sentinel Firewall → Network  
User → App → Permission Request → Sentinel → Allow/Deny  
Sentinel → Local Logs (Encrypted)

## 4. Security Model
- No cloud
- No telemetry
- No external dependencies
- Local encryption (AES‑256)
